  "body": "# Problem\n\nThe current implementation of the chat onboarding tooltip has issues that relate to scrolling. \n\n- First, if the list of chats is empty, the screen can't be scrolled. This should be fixed to accommodate scrolling, when the list is empty.\n\n- Secondly, after the tooltip is dismissed, the list still counts its height for the purpose of scrolling. This can be best observed on the video below\n\n- Third, the tooltip doesn't have the bottom margin of 64, it should be possible to scroll so it's not covered by the + button.\n\n[Link to video demonstrating issues](https://www.dropbox.com/s/7kn9gcnj26g0sx8/onboardingscroll.mp4?dl=0)\n\n## Implementation\n\nImplement the tooltip properly so it behaves just like a regular item on a scrollable list\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\nAll of the above were fixed\n\n## Notes\n\nThank you kindly!",
